:touch
$
$Information
$
!c;How To Play
!a;History of XZR
!b;Characters
#end
:a
XZR/Exile was a brilliant action-rpg
series by Telenet, which began on MSX, and
was ported to PC Engine, and the Sega
Megadrive. Sporting great gameplay and a
controversial storyline, XZR is one of my
favorite RPG series. Here's a brief
description of each game.

XZR - MSX - Japan Only
The original XZR...seems decent, yet
excruciatingly hard. I'm not sure about
all the details of the storyline, as it's
all in Japanese, and very hard to find
info on it on the web. All I know about
it is that it features Sadler during his
work as an assassin, and later on, he
travels to the future for some...
assassinations of political figures (and
dictators) we all know quite well. Also,
IT HAS ZOMBIES AARHGHRGH

XZR II/Exile - MSX, PC Engine, Megadrive
The sequel to XZR, and apparently best
game in the series. Coincidentally, this
is the game you're playing right now. The
Megadrive translation is pretty bad, and
completely eradicates the entire
religious warfare plot. The MSX version
had horribly designed dungeons that would
sometimes literally loop, and with
absence of the escape spell in this
version, makes leaving a dungeon
impossible at times, though I have
managed to beat it. It has a different
ending than the other two versions, with
a confrontation in modern-day New York.
I'd love to see it in English.

Exile 2: Wicked Phenomenon - PC Engine
I recently picked this up, and I was
surprised when i saw that the storyline
wasn't half as good as this game's. Dark
forces have taken over the land and are
driving people crazy, etc etc. Nice
cutscenes, however. And the difficulty
level is ridiculously hard.
#end
:b
$
$Characters
$
$
Sadler
$A former assassin. A man with a free
$mind, he has led the most famous recent
$revolts against various corrupt powers in
$the Chaltar world. He is staying in the
$village of assassins at the beginning of
$this story.
$
Rumi
$Rumi is Sadler's closest friend. She
$seems to be his love interest, as well.
$She's very skilled in acrobatics, and has
$mastered 8 languages. At the beginning of
$the story, she hears that a member of
$Dunes Cavalry has been spotted in the
$surrounding area, and sets off to find
$Sadler, to help her continue the
$investigation.
$
Fakhyle
$An old wizard friend of Sadler's,
$Fakhyle has accompanied him on many a
$trip. A skilled magician, he has
$mastered the mystic stone of Kamiri, no
$longer needing it to cast spells.
$
Kindi
$Fakhyle's mute companion, and friend of
$the group. Though he cannot speak much,
$he has the strength of ten.
$
Yuug D'Payne
$Yuug is the commander of the Dunes
$Cavalry, a branch of the French foreign
$leigon. He disapproves with the measures
$taken by the Klispin Crusaders. In
$attempts to convert the land to their
$religion, they slaughter innocent people,
$and burn entire cities to the ground. To
$stop this horrifying crusade, Yuug needs
$the power of the Holimax, an ancient
$mystic artifact that will unite the world
$under one god. To obtain this elusive
$item, he enlists the help of Sadler.
$
Sadler will meet many more people on his
quest. But as to not spoil the game, they
are not listed here.
#end
:c
How To Play
$
!hc;Buying and Using "Tonics"
!ha;RPG Mode
!hb;Action Mode
#end
:ha
$
$R P G M O D E
In RPG Mode, you spend your time walking
around various areas, collecting
information, conversing with various
characters, and buying tonics. Be sure to
talk to everybody, to get the full story.
#end
:hb
$A C T I O N M O D E
Action mode is your typical ZZT Action-RPG
dungeon, where you run into your enemy to
damage them. Later on, you'll earn magic,
meanning you'll be able to shoot at your
enemy, in the typical ZZT style. Also, in
action mode, you can see a description of
your enemies in the area by pressing ? +m
You're also able to use tonics you've
purchased in town by pressing ? +tonic
#end
:hc
$B U Y I N G / U S I N G T O N I C S
In town, you're able to buy tonics at the
pharmacy. You're only able to carry one
of each tonic at a time, and you may use
them in dungeon sequences by prssing ?
+tonic . Tonics are used to heal HP, and
later on, heal MP.
#end

